.TH "usb_create_shared_hcd" 9 "usb_create_shared_hcd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_create_shared_hcd \- create and initialize an HCD structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct usb_hcd *" usb_create_shared_hcd
.BI "(const struct hc_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *bus_name "  ","
.BI "struct usb_hcd *primary_hcd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "driver" 12
HC driver that will use this hcd
.IP "dev" 12
device for this HC, stored in hcd->self.controller
.IP "bus_name" 12
value to store in hcd->self.bus_name
.IP "primary_hcd" 12
a pointer to the usb_hcd structure that is sharing the
PCI device.  Only allocate certain resources for the primary HCD
.SH "CONTEXT"
task context, might sleep.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a struct usb_hcd, with extra space at the end for the
HC driver's private data.  Initialize the generic members of the
hcd structure.
.SH "RETURN"
On success, a pointer to the created and initialized HCD structure.
On failure (e.g. if memory is unavailable), NULL.
